''Opus Eponymous'' entered the [[Sverigetopplistan]] Albums Top 60 chart at number 59, staying on the charts for 5 weeks and peaking at number 50.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acharts.us/album/58604 |title=Ghost - Opus Eponymous |publisher=acharts.us |accessdate=2012-02-22}}</ref> The album was nominated for the [[Grammis|Grammis Award]] (the Swedish equivalent to the [[Grammy Award]]s) in the "Best Hard Rock" category.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://legacy.roadrunnerrecords.com/blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=152465 |title=WATAIN Wins Swedish GRAMMIS Award For 'Best Hard Rock' Album |publisher=blabbermouth.net |date=2011-04-06 |accessdate=2012-02-21}}</ref> In the June 2011 edition of ''Sweden Rock Magazine'' it was named the third best album in the past decade, with the first two being ''[[The Final Frontier (album)|The Final Frontier]]'' and ''[[A Matter of Life and Death (album)|A Matter of Life and Death]]'' by [[Iron Maiden]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.swedenrockmagazine.com/index.cfm?pg=100 |title=Storslam f<U+00F6>r Sverigeaktuella IRON MAIDEN n<U+00E4>r SWEDEN ROCK MAGAZINE firar tio <U+00E5>r! |publisher=Sweden Rock Magazine |accessdate=2012-02-21}}</ref> The album's cover was declared the fourth best of 2010 by ''[[Revolver (magazine)|Revolver]]'' magazine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.revolvermag.com/uncategorized/final-six-the-six-best-worst-album-covers-of-2010.html |title=Final Six: The Six Best/Worst Album Covers of 2010 |publisher=revolvermag.com |date=2010-12-23 |accessdate=2012-02-21}}</ref>

